I'm just putting in my intial -1 comments that I shared privately here and that newer patches should be addressing.

I was trying to verify https://bugs.launchpad.net/glance/+bug/1367771 today and I just can’t seem to make it work.  I did a brand new devstack and then did the following and I’m still seeing errors if I run the glance-manage db_load_metadefs twice.  I expected that if I ran it a second time, that it would just not load any namespaces that are pre-existing in the database with just a simple error like “Skipping  namespace %s. It already exists in the database.”  Perhaps we could add some --reload flag.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

I might have a few nitpicks on code formatting, but I don't see any blockers in here.  I tested numerous scenarios from command line and everything worked as expected. The following are scenarios I tested and worked for me.

Empty DB
All namespaces being previously loaded.
All but one namespace being previously loaded.
Modifying an existing namespace and ensuring that the load doesn't overwrite the modified data.

I know that you are working on a followup patch for testing the glance-manage load and unload commands, so please include the above scenarios in that patch.
